    <td class="xl66" height="440" align="right" style='height:264.00pt;' x:num>44756</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>[Chat Module - Supplier Dashboard] Implement Dynamic Text Truncation for Chat Messages</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Add logic to handle and display long text messages within the chat interface. The system should differentiate between continuous long text (without spaces) and normal sentences (with spaces), applying specific truncation rules for each case to ensure clean display and prevent layout breaks. Acceptance Criteria: Continuous Text Handling (No Spaces): If the input text is a single continuous string with no spaces (e.g., “hellooooooooooooooo”), display only the first 10 characters.Append &quot;...&quot; at the end of the truncated text.Example: Input: helloooooooooooooooOutput: helloooooo... &amp;#91;*&amp;#93; Sentence Handling (With Spaces): If the text contains spaces, display only the first 2 words followed by &quot;...&quot;.Example: Input: Hello there, how are you?Output: Hello there...</td>
