   <tr height="682.50" style='height:409.50pt;'>
    <td class="xl66" height="682.50" align="right" style='height:409.50pt;' x:num>45642</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>[Admin-1] User Story: Settings Management</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>As an Admin I want to manage platform settings from the Settings page So that I can control system configurations from one place. Description The Settings screen contains multiple setting cards/sections where the Admin can: Update general platform informationConfigure system optionsToggle activation statusEdit configurable valuesSave changes per section Each settings block appears as a separate card with editable fields and a Save button. ✅ Acceptance Criteria 1️⃣ Access Control Only Admin users can access the Settings page.Unauthorized users cannot view the page. 2️⃣ Editable Settings Sections Settings are displayed in grouped cards.Each card contains: Input fields (text / number).Toggle buttons (Enable / Disable).Status indicators (Active / Inactive badges).Save button for that section. 3️⃣ Field Behavior Input fields: Support inline validation.Show error messages for invalid values. Toggle buttons: Change status visually (Active / Inactive).Update value on save. Disabled settings appear visually different from active ones. 4️⃣ Save Action Clicking Save: Validates all fields in the section.Shows loading state.Displays success message on success.Displays error message if request fails. Changes persist after page refresh.</td>
    <td class="xl68" align="right" x:num="46329.555034722223">03/11/2026 13:19</td>
    <td class="xl68" align="right" x:num="46329.">03/11/2026 00:00</td>
