   <tr height="682.50" style='height:409.50pt;'>
    <td class="xl66" height="682.50" align="right" style='height:409.50pt;' x:num>45836</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>[Merchant-1] User Story – EXW Checkout</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Customer selects EXW (Ex Works) as shipping method during checkout As a Customer I want to Choose EXW shipping method when placing an order So that I can handle the pickup, shipping, and logistics myself from the seller’s warehouse Description When the customer selects EXW (Ex Works) during checkout: The seller is responsible only for preparing the goods.The customer is responsible for: Pickup from warehouseShipping arrangementCustoms clearanceExport/import documentationShipping fees ✅ Acceptance Criteria 1️- Shipping Method Selection EXW option appears in shipping methods (if enabled by seller).Customer can select EXW before proceeding to payment. 2️ Address Handling Delivery address field becomes: Optional OR hidden (based on business rules). Pickup location (seller warehouse address) is clearly displayed. 3- Order Confirmation Order summary clearly shows: Shipping Method: EXWPickup Location details Customer must confirm acknowledgment: “I understand that I am responsible for pickup and shipping.” (Checkbox required before payment) 5️⃣ Order Status Flow After successful payment: Order status becomes: Ready for PickupSeller can: Upload pickup detailsShare warehouse contact info Customer can: Mark order as “Picked Up”</td>
