    <td class="xl66" x:str>Title: Manage Membership for Suppliers As a Super Admin I want to manage the Membership configuration and assign it to suppliers So that all suppliers have a membership level that controls their participation in the platform. Description The system will contain a Membership module where the Super Admin can manage membership details. The system will initially contain one default membership created through a seed. All newly registered suppliers will automatically receive the default membership. The Super Admin can later update the membership details or change the membership assigned to a supplier. Acceptance Criteria The system must contain one default membership created through a seed during system setup.The Membership module must include the following fields: Name (Arabic)Name (English)PhotoStatus (Active / Deactive) The Super Admin can: View membership detailsAdd membership (if none exists)Edit membershipDelete membership The system must not allow more than one membership record at the same time.When a new supplier is created or registered, the system automatically assigns the default membership.The Super Admin can change the membership assigned to a supplier from the Admin Dashboard.Membership can be activated or deactivated by the Super Admin.Only users with the Super Admin role can manage the Membership module.</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>03/15/2026 07:01:53 pm</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>03/15/2026 07:00:00 pm</td>
