   <tr height="380" style='height:228.00pt;'>
    <td class="xl66" height="380" align="right" style='height:228.00pt;' x:num>46364</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Email validation error message displayed differently in front end</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Description: The error message for email validation returned from the back end is displayed differently in the front end. When the user enters an invalid email format, the message shown on the front end does not match the error message sent by the back end. This causes inconsistency between the back-end validation response and the message displayed to the user. Actual Result: The error message displayed on the front end is different from the error message returned by the back end.(The email address must be a valid email address.) Expected Result: The front end should display the same validation error message returned from the back end to maintain consistency.(Validation failed!)</td>
