   <tr height="340" style='height:204.00pt;'>
    <td class="xl66" height="340" align="right" style='height:204.00pt;' x:num>46380</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>English and special characters allowed in Merchant Terms &amp; Conditions (AR) fieldEnglish and special characters allowed in Terms &amp; Conditions (AR) field</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Description: In the Terms &amp; Conditions (AR) section, the system allows users to enter English letters and special characters even though the field is intended for Arabic content. The field should validate the input to ensure that only Arabic text is entered. However, currently the system accepts English text and symbols without showing any validation error. Actual Result: The system accepts English text and special characters without any validation. Expected Result: The system should restrict the input to Arabic characters only and show a validation message if English text or special characters are entered.</td>
