   <tr height="682.50" style='height:409.50pt;'>
    <td class="xl66" height="682.50" align="right" style='height:409.50pt;' x:num>46506</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>[Userstory] FCA Trade Term Order Handling</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Title: Handle FCA Shipping for Multiple Warehousing Locations As a Merchant I want to choose the warehousing location and the quantity of products delivered to each location when ordering products with the FCA trade term So that the supplier can deliver the products to the correct warehouse locations according to the merchant’s shipping plan. Description When a merchant creates an order containing products with the FCA (Free Carrier) trade term, the merchant is responsible for selecting the delivery warehouse location where the supplier will hand over the goods. If the order contains multiple quantities of a product, the merchant can distribute the quantities across different warehouse addresses. For example: If the merchant orders 3 products, the merchant can choose which warehouse(s) will receive the shipment and specify the quantity delivered to each warehouse. Scenario Merchant adds 3 products with FCA trade term to the cart.During checkout, the Shipping Details section appears.The system displays the merchant’s saved warehouse addresses.The merchant selects one or more warehouses.The merchant enters the quantity of products to ship to each warehouse.The total quantity distributed across warehouses must equal the total ordered quantity. Acceptance Criteria 1. FCA Shipping Section When the product trade term is FCA, the Shipping Details section appears in checkout. 2. Warehouse Selection The merchant can: View available warehouse addresses.Select one or multiple warehouses for delivery. Each warehouse card includes: Warehouse nameAddressQuantity input field 3. Quantity Distribution The merchant must enter: Quantity to ship to each warehouse Rules: Quantity must be greater than 0Total distributed quantity must equal the ordered quantity Example: [th]Warehouse [/th][th]Quantity [/th]Riyadh Dry Port 1 Jeddah Port 2 Total = 3 product</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>03/17/2026 07:00:07 pm</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>03/18/2026 07:00:00 pm</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Ahmed Abdelfattah</td>
    <td class="xl66" x:str>Hesham Raafat</td>
