    <td class="xl66" x:str>Description: When the user tries to reset the password, the system sends an OTP to the email. After entering the received OTP, the system displays that the OTP is incorrect even though the correct OTP was entered. Expected Result: The system should accept the correct OTP and allow the user to proceed with resetting the password. Actual Result: The system shows an error message indicating that the OTP is incorrect even when the correct OTP is entered.</td>
